article.headline: New Hampshire 78, Cent. Connecticut St. 70
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Mike Christensen scored a game-high 23 points and New Hampshire shot 14-for-26 from 3-point range for a 78-70 win over Central Connecticut State on Saturday night. Tristan Blackwood led central with 19 points. Central (0-3) used an 8-0 run to pull within 70-67 with 2:30 to play, but Christensen and Tyrece hit 3-pointers around a free throw to give the Wildcats (2-1) a 76-68 lead. New Hampshire made 6-of-9 3-pointers in the first half for a 40-33 halftime lead. Alvin Abreu scored 14 and Gibbs finished with 13 for New Hampshire.
